## 21. Troubleshooting

| Symptom | Cause / fix |
|---|---|
| "Header 'Trade ID' was not found" | The header cell text isn't exactly `Trade ID` (extra space, typo). |
| "No source workbook selected" | Click **Browse Workbook** first. |
| "source file no longer exists" | It was moved/renamed — browse again. |
| "No table containing 'Barclays Trade ID'" | Source columns must be inside real Excel **Tables** (Ctrl+T) with that exact header. |
| Some IDs show as not found | ID truly absent, or formatting mismatch (leading apostrophe, spaces). `NormID` trims and de-scientifics integers; clean stray spaces. |
| Headers got created in the wrong place | Output starts one column right of the `Trade ID` header — ensure that column is clear before the first run. |
| Wrong file reused | Two open files share a base name; close the unintended one. |
| Excel feels frozen after an error | Re-run any macro (it calls `FastModeOff`), or just reopen the workbook (Workbook_Open restores settings). |

## 22. Why it's fast

- **Arrays, not cells:** each table body is read once with a single
  `.Value` call; matching happens in memory — no cell-by-cell looping.
- **Dictionaries:** O(1) ID lookups; duplicates are searched once and filled
  for every occurrence.
- **Early exit:** uniqueness across the workbook means the scan stops the
  instant the last pending ID is found.
- **Bulk write:** all results land in one array-to-range assignment.
- **No Select/Activate/Copy-Paste;** ScreenUpdating/Events/Calc disabled during
  the run and always restored.

